It is conditioning us, okay?

207
00:21:30,107 --> 00:21:32,392
So time moves on, as always.

208
00:21:33,795 --> 00:21:36,759
So let me finish with another little paragraph.

209
00:21:36,901 --> 00:21:39,444
This is a slightly different way of looking at it.

210
00:21:43,874 --> 00:21:48,301
If there is lust for nutriment, edible food,

211
00:21:48,451 --> 00:22:02,526
If there is lust for nutriment-edible food, if there is delight, if there is craving, consciousness becomes established there and comes to grow.

212
00:22:02,566 --> 00:22:03,666
Okay?

213
00:22:03,686 --> 00:22:05,950
So, I mean, that's what we experience, isn't it?

214
00:22:05,970 --> 00:22:14,778
The more we feed our greed, etc., etc., the more we want of it, no matter what the greed is of, right?

215
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:18,854
These days, people just want more.

216
00:22:19,153 --> 00:22:20,175
It doesn't matter what it is.

217
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:21,277
It's just more.

218
00:22:21,477 --> 00:22:26,284
I mean, that's what we've come to want, you see, just more of anything.

219
00:22:27,766 --> 00:22:34,875
Wherever consciousness becomes established and comes to grow, there is a descent into name and form, body and mind.

220
00:22:35,295 --> 00:22:36,517
Notice that the descent.

221
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:44,547
I don't quite understand the image there as to why he says descent, but I presume it's a case of...

222
00:22:45,926 --> 00:22:50,753
that it's something which is not to be desired.

223
00:22:50,954 --> 00:22:54,680
So remember, nibbana is something beyond all this, right?

224
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:56,363
That's difficult for us to accept.

225
00:22:59,928 --> 00:23:06,176
Where there is a descent into name and form, body and mind, there is a growth of volitional formation.

226
00:23:06,277 --> 00:23:14,769
So as soon as we have this psychophysical organism, then we want to do, we want to act, and that's our volition.

227
00:23:15,256 --> 00:23:24,761
Where there is a growth of volitional formations, there's the production of future renewed existence, moment after moment, and if you will, life after life.

228
00:23:25,463 --> 00:23:31,240
And where there is a production of future renewed existence, there is future birth, aging, and death.

229
00:23:31,777 --> 00:23:39,473
Where there is future birth, aging, and death, I say, that is accompanied by sorrow, anguish, and despair.

230
00:23:40,355 --> 00:23:48,874
So he's actually asking us to contemplate our lives from these four nutriment points of view to become aware

231
00:23:49,292 --> 00:24:08,887
of what we're actually eating for the body's sake, that we're not getting attached to food, that we're aware of the feelings that arise when we make contact with anything, that we're aware of the process of attention and intention which creates karma for us,

232
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:17,583
and that we're aware of how consciousness is the window or the mirror in which we enter into the world.

233
00:24:17,623 --> 00:24:22,431
So it's very important to recognize where we put our attention.

234
00:24:24,775 --> 00:24:25,336
Very good.

235
00:24:25,537 --> 00:24:28,080
So I hope my words have been of some assistance there.

236
00:24:28,121 --> 00:24:30,184
They've not caused even greater confusion.

237
00:24:31,727 --> 00:24:34,352
And it's time to do a bit of meditation, I think.

